description: Welcome to Yerba Buena lofts, where luxury and comfort are blended to create the perfect living experience. Located on the top floor, unit #924 is a stunning space that offers breathtaking city views from its oversized windows. As you enter the unit, you'll be impressed with the soaring 20'+ ceilings and the open floor plan that provides ample space for living and entertaining. The living room leads to a patio, which is the perfect spot to unwind and enjoy the stunning city views. The sleek and modern kitchen is equipped with high-end stainless steel appliances and an abundance of counter space. The kitchen effortlessly flows into the living and dining area, making it an ideal space for hosting guests. The bedroom is spacious and comes with a huge walk-in closet that can be transformed into a creative space to suit your personal needs. The unit also includes 1.5 bathrooms, adding to its convenience and functionality. The building has a doorman, providing you with peace of mind and a warm welcome every time you return home. Additionally, the unit includes a parking spot, which is both convenient and rare in San Francisco. Located in the vibrant and bustling neighborhood of Yerba Buena, you'll enjoy easy access to museums, Cal-Train, the subway, and shopping.

Stunning  loft style view condo in Hawthorne Place. This spacious light filled 1 bedroom, 1.5 bath condo features an open floor plan, boasting of 17' ceilings, large windows, exposed concrete and hardwood floors. On the main floor you will find the kitchen with granite counters, a powder room, in unit laundry, and a spacious living/dining area. A staircase leads up to the primary suite containing a full bathroom, walk-in closet, and separate entry. One car parking in garage is included. Centrally located and within easy walking distance to jobs, transportation, AT&T, Moscone Center, SFMOMA and so much more.

This Mission Dolores/Dolores Heights condo has it all!  2 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, 1 car independent garage parking, in-unit washer/dryer, and private balcony. Constructed in 2003, this condo has a great open floor plan, gas burning fireplace, generous sized closets, recessed lighting, and crown moldings. The kitchen is equipped with stainless appliances, including a gas range, dishwasher, microwave and refrigerator. The very spacious primary bedroom has a large closet, bathroom with soaking tub, and dual sinks. The second bedroom is versatile and can be used for guests, as an office or as desired. The unit has been freshly painted. Best of all, it's steps from the vibrant food and boutique scene along the Valencia Street corridor and 2 blocks to Mission Dolores Park.  Overall, it's a great buy in a great neighborhood!

Video Preview! Built in 2002 The Village at Petrini Place is 134 condominiums in Prime NOPA across the street from USF & Lone Mountain. Unit 232 is a spacious 2 bedroom - 2 bathroom home facing south overlooking the inner courtyard. Enter past a coat closet into The bright open living area with Maple hardwood floors. There is a private balcony on the south west corner of the home. The kitchen has granite countertops & stainless steel appliances. The washer dryer is conveniently located at the beginning of the hallway to the bedrooms. The bright first bedroom is across the hall from a bathroom with a shower over a tub. The primary bedroom suite has a walk-in closet. The bathroom has double sinks & a large shower. There is One deeded parking space in the secure garage with elevator access. This Beautiful fitness room is off the lobby. Petrini Place is convenient Urban living in the Center of San Francisco.

TRANSPARENT PRICE!! Enjoy the Vibrant Energy of the NOPA Neighborhood. This large contemporary 2BD/2BA unit, located at the Village at Petrini Place, features a modern kitchen with granite counter, generous cabinetry, and eat-in counter. There is an enormous patio, south facing and private, with access through the living/dining room. The living/dining room has wood floors and bedrooms are carpeted. The unit also highlights a generous master suit with a huge walk-in closet and bathroom. In-unit laundry hook-ups and hallway closets complete the interior of the unit. A notable feature is a TWO-car parking, an incredible value.  There is a courtyard with potted trees, flowers, and chairs in a quiet setting. Building amenities include a gym, club room, and on-site management. Excellent location for public transit, corporate shuttle routes, Downtown, and proximity to G. G. Park Panhandle; plenty of grocery stores and eateries to choose from.

Residence 3F is a unique offering at nearly 2,000 square feet, comprised of 3-Bed, 3-Bath, & 3-Balconies. This large floorplan is wrapped in windows throughout, filling the home with natural light & providing stunning outlooks. As you enter through the formal hallway you are greeted by a large open kitchen, dining, & living room. The contemporary kitchen showcases a large eat-in island, integrated cabinetry and top-of-the-line Gaggenau appliances. The kitchen seamlessly leads out to a charming breakfast balcony, perfect for enjoying morning meals in the fresh air. The dining room is great for formal or everyday meals. The living room is spacious & leads to a viewing deck overlooking the city skyline. All three bedrooms have large walk-in closets. The primary bedroom also features a room for a desk & a spacious bathroom with dual vanity sinks, separate shower & bathtub. The second suite has its own bathroom & private balcony. There is a laundry closet with Bosch washer & dryer. One car valet parking space is included. Considered to be one of the best amenities focused buildings on the West Coast, Lumina has over an acre of 5-Star facilities incl. a gym, spa, massage room, 70-ft lap pool, owner's lounge, game room, movie theatre, roof deck, & Woodlands Market.

Imagine waking up every morning, walking out your front door and taking a stroll through Alta Plaza park on your way to get a hot cup of coffee and a freshly baked croissant at any of the nearby iconic establishments. Once you're fueled up, pop into any of the prestigious boutiques along Fillmore, stop by Mollie Stones for some fresh groceries, or - if you're looking for a bit more exercise - get your heart pumping with a run through the Presidio and the famous Lyon St steps. Once you head home, you'll be in awe of your quiet oasis, tucked away from the bustle of California Street. The cozy fireplace adds warmth and charm to the open living area, and the stunning, top-of-the-line kitchen is sure to impress even the most discerning chefs. With tons of natural light, a shared yard, a gorgeous marble bathroom, and high-end upgrades throughout, you'll be the envy of all your friends. Welcome home!

This newly renovated top floor 2BD/2BA condo features an open plan living area w/wood burning fireplace & dramatic wall of windows, & city views. Sliding glass doors open to a large private deck. The kitchen has been remodeled w/custom cabinetry & granite countertops w/bar, stainless steel appliances, including Viking stove & hood, KitchenAid refrigerator, & Miele dishwasher. A skylight above the kitchen floods the room with natural light. The large primary bedroom with ample closet space has an en-suite bath w/shower over tub & Carrera style tile surround, custom vanity with quartz countertops, & skylight overhead. The second bedroom also has generous closet space and an en-suite bath, has nice southerly views & direct access to the large deck. The guest bath, accessible from the second bedroom or hallway, has a large custom vanity w/quartz counters, skylight & separate room with walk-in shower & custom Carrera style tile & separate linen closet. Add'l features include newly installed engineered hardwood flooring, formal entry w/skylight & coat closet, double paned windows, fresh paint, common laundry, deeded storage & 1 car pkg. Condo is ideally situated at the intersection of Nob and Russian Hill, steps from many popular shops and restaurants on vibrant Polk Street.

Price Improvement! Located in The Beacon, a luxurious full amenity building in desirable Mission Bay neighborhood. This meticulously maintained residence ensures a lifestyle of comfort and convenience. 2 BD/2BA, bright and inviting condo with open floorplan. Large windows flood the interior with natural sunlight. Expansive 240 sq. ft. terrace, where you can relish in indoor/outdoor living and unlock endless possibilities for relaxation and entertainment. Updated kitchen featuring granite countertops and stainless-steel appliances. The high-end French Oak plank flooring adds a touch of elegance to the space, while the in-unit washer and dryer provide convenience. The Beacon offers a level of luxury living, with a 24-hour concierge and an array of amenities, including, a heated outdoor pool and spa, club lounge, gym, business center, and outdoor dog park. A designated spot in the parking garage ensures convenient hassle-free parking. Perfectly situated in an urban haven, this condo is just steps away from groceries, restaurants, boutiques, luxury bowling alley and highway access. Explore the thriving Mission Bay area, where the renowned Chase Center and Oracle Park awaits. Commuting is a breeze with Muni, bus lines, and Caltrain all within one block, making it a commuter's dream.

Located in prime Noe Valley, mere blocks from 24th St., your private oasis awaits. Flooded with light from windows on 3 sides, this condominium offers a beautifully flowing layout updated with top notch finishes while still maintaining beautiful classical details. Two bedrooms and 2-full bathrooms with ample living space, and a shared outdoor space for your morning coffee or WFH. With gorgeous hardwoods, beautiful light throughout, an updated eat-in kitchen, and a recently updated primary bathroom, you're sure to fall in love with this charming unit! The eat-in kitchen is dreamy with newer stainless steel appliances, beautiful marble counter tops and updated overhead lighting. One side-by-side parking space in the garage with plenty of storage, and your own laundry seals the deal. Perfectly situated between Noe Valley's 24th Street and Valencia St/Mission restaurants and shopping including Novy, Beretta, Firefly and Saru. Close to Dolores Park and the Noe Valley Recreation Center and easy access to J-Church, multiple Muni buses, and 280/101 make commuting a breeze!  This home is a do not miss opportunity to be in one of the most sought-after pockets of San Francisco!

**Last unit remaining!** The ParksideSF features 13 generous condos ranging from one to three bedrooms. Unit 103 is located on the 3rd floor. Extensively updated, this unit offers San Francisco living at its finest, at every step. The updated kitchen has everything you need: gorgeous porcelain slab countertops and backsplash, a statement waterfall breakfast bar, modern cabinetry, and high-end stainless steel appliances from Thermador, Fisher & Paykel and Bosch. Parking and storage is available for every unit. Elevator in the building and secured bike room.

A beautiful light-filled corner residence,facing the pool in the sought-after North Waterfront neighborhood. Peek-a-boo views of coit tower and downtown. The living room opens to a large sunny deck facing the gardens and pool. Beautiful wood-burning fireplace. High ceilings. New appliances, carpets, and fresh paint. The spacious primary suite looks out to the gardens and the financial district and has a huge walk-in closet.  Amenities include a 24/7-hour Security/Doorman, Pool, Spa, Landscaped gardens, and conference & Club room.  Come home to the easy lifestyle living at 101 Lombard.

World-Class views of Golden Gate Bridge, Bay Bridge, San Francisco Skyline and beyond from a premiere Russian Hill doorman high-rise, The Summit! The versatile floor plan was created by combining two units #2903 and #2905. The signature floor-to-ceiling glass walls of this ultra-luxury high-floor Northeast corner residence frame incredibly sky-high 3-bridge, 4-county views from the Golden Gate Bridge to Bay Bridge, from the San Francisco Skyline to the Marin Headlands and beyond. Floating high above the Magical City-by-The-Bay'' this gracious residence enjoys postcard-like views of San Francisco's world-renowned landmarks and the ever-changing beauty of the Bay    Featuring generous entertaining spaces, 2 large bedrooms plus den, 2 full bathrooms, step-out terrace and a timeless contemporary design, this is a wonderful home to enjoy a quintessentially urban lifestyle in one of the City's most desirable and historic residential neighborhoods.

Sophisticated 2BR/1BA condo in the heart of Upper Fillmore! Enter your new home through a tiered fragrant courtyard with chirping birds and awash in all-day sun. Private patio entrance invites lazing around in a secluded sitting area. Inside, excellent floorplan spreads out across one level and includes en-suite primary BR, second BR, LR/DR combination and efficient kitchen with pass-through. Classy upgrades like custom wood cabinets and stone countertops in kitchen and bath, stainless appliances, wood-burning FP with stone surround and hearth, and built-in storage cabinet in living room put this home a cut above ordinary condos. Bay window in DR creates more space for sumptuous dinners, and tree-shaded balcony off living room is your own private roost for watching what's happening on Fillmore Street. In-unit W/D, generous closets, pet-friendly building, one-car deeded garage parking, new carpet and fresh paint make this home truly move-in ready. Central location offers close proximity to exciting shops, cafes, restaurants, boutiques, farmer's markets and entertainment venues, as well as numerous transportation choices and quick access to downtown and 101. Ditch your diet and visit the Fillmore Bakeshop downstairs for fresh croissants, cookies and pies. This is home.

Stunning rarely available ocean front views from this 3 bedroom/2 bath unit in a boutique building.    Imagine relaxing by the sea as you watch the sun set over the ocean, strolling along the beach, surfing or parasailing the iconic Ocean Beach waves!    Gourmet renovated kitchen, with recessed lighting, stainless steel appliances, fresh paint and new flooring throughout allow for endless entertaining.    The generous living room has a huge bay window facing the Pacific Ocean, allowing for spectacular sunsets over the sea.    The spacious primary suite includes an ensuite bath, 2 closets and a garden view, with 2 additional generous bedrooms.  In unit side-by side laundry.    Set in an established neighborhood, where neighbors share a love of the ocean, this is truly a rare find.    Shared yard.  Garage: 1 car garage parking and 1 parking permit for the private street.  This exceptional location is close to Golden Gate Park, Sutro Heights, Lands End hiking trails, grocery,  MUNI, the VA Medical Center and the many shops and restaurants on Balboa Street.

Price Drop-Motivated Seller! Welcome to this modern, tri-level, 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom live/work loft located in the heart of San Francisco's SOMA neighborhood on a well kept, tree-lined street. Unit has been renovated to include new hardwood flooring, new appliances, new quartz counters in kitchen and bath, new tile and fresh modern paint.  This beautiful loft features open, spacious living, dining and kitchen layout with floor to ceiling windows, gas fireplace and balcony. The upper level is a large bedroom (fits a king bed as seen in photo) with two closets including a walk-in and ensuite bathroom. The lower floor features a spacious bedroom or work space with closet, storage and direct street access. The second full bathroom inches a shower over spa tub and all new tile.  Double stacker laundry IN UNIT.  One deeded parking space (SUV OK) and storage locker. LOW HOA: $556 per month. Water and sewer included.  Web pass internet. Guest parking. Shared roof deck with gas grill.  Minutes from the Ball Park, Embarcadero and Safeway.  Easy access to 280/101.

NEW PRICE! COME & GET IT!  Light, volume and location in this rarely available 1st floor home! Yerba Buena Lofts has always been celebrated for it's architecture, and this loft features all of the signature touches from starchitect Stanley Saitowitz: dramatic walls of glass, exposed concrete for a cool industrial vibe, and a private outdoor terrace. In addition, you'll find a host of thoughtful upgrades throughout. A private entrance from Folsom makes this uniquely versatile. Soaring ceilings add drama to the open living room and kitchen, and upstairs the sleeping area has a luxurious amount of closet space. Building amenities include: 24-Hour security, secure lobby, on-site management, and a full-time engineer & maintenance staff. Nearly perfect WalkScore means the ultimate in city convenience. Whole Foods, Metreon, Trader Joes, Financial District, Ball Park, FiDi & Embarcadero all at your doorstep. A private parking spot plus in-unit laundry complete the package.

3 bedroom, 2 bath, 1 parking Below Market Rate (BMR) housing opportunity available at 100% Area Median Income (AMI). Maximum income for 3 people = $124,700; 4 = $138,550; 5 = $149,650; 6 = $160,700, etc. Must be 1st-time homebuyer & income eligible. Unit available thru the Mayor's Office of Housing and Community Development (MOHCD) & subject to resale controls, monitoring & other restrictions. Unit will be listed on DAHLIA, the SF Housing Portal (https://housing.sfgov.org) starting on the application date, Thursday, March 9th, 2023. Visit https://housing.sfgov.org for application & program info. Application, loan pre-approval, and homebuyer education verification due on Thursday, March 30th, 2023 at 5:00 PM. Open house times Saturday, March 18 - 12-2pm, Tuesday, March 21 - 2-4pm, Friday, March 24 - 5-7pm.

Light filled 5-bedroom, 3-bath house-like 2-level upper townhome situated in a 2-unit building with San Francisco Grand Victorian charm, featuring hardwood floors, ornate wainscoting, moldings and trim. Living Room, Formal Dining Room plus large Family Room with Golden Gate, Marin Headlands, and City views has everything today's urban dweller needs. Flexible floor plan allows for family or multi-generational living or generous entertaining and separate office spaces for the working professional. Beautifully maintained over the last 50+ years by the same family. Updating in the 80's and 90's included some plumbing, electrical and many windows. A full basement offers great possibility for garage addition. Ideal location with Golden Gate Park at your front doorstep and Lone Mountain hilltop 55-acre USF campus and St Ignatius. Easy transportation provided by MUNI and private shuttles. Whole Foods and Cole Valley, NOPA and the Haight are just a few blocks away. Costs of new TIC agreement to be shared. Possible condo conversion?

This elegant and luxurious condo overlooks a serene manicured courtyard and presents an incredible sense of calm and spaciousness. The well-appointed and flexible open layout is ideal for entertainment and provides an abundance of living space. Extensively renovated, Unit 307 features European white oak wood floors, a beautifully modern kitchen with Carrara marble countertops and stainless steel appliances, high-end range, wood-burning fireplace in the living room, renovated modern bathroom with marble tile surround, and private patio with barbecue space. This beautifully maintained elevator building features secure garage parking, updated contemporary lobby, shared sauna, and incredible landscaped private courtyard where pets can play and residents can enjoy reading benches which sit beneath mature trees and open sky. Unit 307 also includes a large private storage unit, which is spacious enough to store bicycles and large sports equipment. With a WalkScore of 99, living at 1440 Broadway is ideal in both convenience and ease. Located in the gorgeous and highly desirable Nob Hill/Polk Gulch neighborhood, Unit 307 is just moments from an abundance of neighborhood amenities, gourmet cafes, fine restaurants, shops, parks, public transportation and much more.  1440broadway307.com

SOMA Grand Residence #911 is a luxurious and spacious one bedroom + den condo in the heart of San Francisco. This stunning condo has expansive windows and open floor plan, kitchen with stainless steel appliances, stone countertops, breakfast bar, & in-unit laundry hook-ups. Enjoy premium, luxury hotel services.  1 Bedroom Below Market Rate (BMR) housing opportunity available at 100% Area Median Income (AMI). Maximum income for 1 person= $97,000; 2 people = $110,850; 3 = $124,700, etc. Must be 1st-time homebuyer & income eligible. Unit available thru the Mayor's Office of Housing and Community Development (MOHCD) & subject to resale controls, monitoring & other restrictions. Unit will be listed on DAHLIA, the SF Housing Portal (https://housing.sfgov.org) starting on the application date, December 12, 2022. Visit https://housing.sfgov.org for application & program info. Application, loan pre-approval, and homebuyer education verification due on 01/04/2023 at 5:00 PM.  Please see the virtual tour at https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=qmZhLeyQzEL

Spacious and stylish, bright and airy two-bedroom home + Den ( perfect for WFH office) - beautifully updated with custom closets, hardwood floors, and high-end finishes, this home is flooded with natural light, the floor-to-ceiling windows also showcase gorgeous water views from the Bay and city views facing the Oracle Park, home to the SF Giants ( front row seat property to enjoy amazing fireworks shows during game season ). The gourmet chef's kitchen is beautifully outfitted with a large island, granite counters, white European cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, and under-cabinet lighting. The spacious primary bedroom boasts a large ensuite, multiple closets, and a generous flex space that can be used as a den/office. The second bedroom is perfect as a guest bedroom/office. BLU is a highly desirable boutique residence with 24/7 front desk personnel/concierge, located in the heart of San Francisco's booming SoMa/ South Beach tech capital, this sophisticated residence is also close to world-class museums, as well as acclaimed dining, cultural, sporting and entertainment attractions - a wonderful urban oasis in the heart of one of the City's most vibrant, safe and secured new neighborhoods! Walker's paradise (96/100), Rider's paradise (100/100), Very bikeable (75/100)

Experience luxury living in the heart of Russian Hill with this exquisite one-bedroom condo in a boutique 3-unit building that boasts the perfect blend of warmth and elegance. The home has an open and airy layout, tall ceilings, a chef's kitchen, and a large dining and living room area that is perfect for both entertaining and everyday living. The gourmet kitchen features a full suite of high-end stainless steel appliances, loads of counter space, generous storage, and custom cabinetry. Relax in the spacious living room that is flooded with natural light and features a built-in home office. The bright bedroom has ample closet space and a spa-like ensuite bathroom. Add'l features incl. secure elevator access directly in to the home, radiant heating, in-unit W/D, alarm system, intercom, 1 car parking, private storage, and a shared yard. Conveniently located steps to notable eateries, shopping, nightlife, public transit, highways, downtown SF and the waterfront, this home is a must see!

City Living at The Artani. Centrally located near the Civic Center and a quick walk to Hayes Valley dining and shopping. This spacious 1 Bedroom | 1 Bathroom condo features high-end finishes throughout. Beech wide plank flooring and upgraded carpet in the bedroom. Chef's kitchen includes stainless appliances, Caesarstone countertops, custom cabinetry, and under cabinet lighting. The Artani is a contemporary boutique building featuring two high-speed elevators, on-site security, an impressive rooftop with BBQ and expansive city views. Building is wired for Google Fiber high-speed internet. In-unit laundry, one-car parking, additional storage and air conditioning are included.

This newly renovated top floor Mission Dolores condominium features all of today's sought after amenities in an incredible location, just 1.5 blocks to Valencia St. Awash in natural light from the multiple skylights, the home boasts 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, 1,420 sqft, with an incredible 360-degree view exclusive-use roof terrace, accessed internally via the retractable skylight door. The open great room is anchored by the professional kitchen with a spacious island wrapped in stone. The living room features a gas-burning fireplace with plenty of space for an additional seating area or desk area, adjacent to the formal dining area. The spa-like bathrooms are adorned with Porcelenosa tile and radiant floor heating. Renovated in 2018, features of this home include air conditioning, white oak flooring, video entry, security alarm, and one car parking in the garage. 99 Walk Score - Whole Foods, Market St, and Dolores Park are all a short walk away.

For the first time in nearly 30 years, one of the most striking and contemporary townhomes is now available. This architectural masterpiece is a sight to behold, with a soaring 17-foot ceiling in the living room and a remarkable greenhouse skylight that bathes the entire space in natural light. The bridge overlook to the living room below is a captivating feature that elevates the elegance of this exceptional residence. Enjoy breathtaking views from every angle and revel in the superb outlooks this unit affords. Spacious 3BR/3BA, bay views, 4 decks, fireplace, extra storage and guest parking. Discover the ultimate in refined urban living at Golden Gateway Commons, where sophistication and convenience are yours to relish.

Elegant Pacific Heights condominium with large, private yard! 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, with classic period detail throughout. At the front of the home is a sunny living room with fireplace, and 2 lovely bedrooms and bath with shower over tub. A modern eat-in kitchen offers a breakfast area, a pantry closet, deluxe stainless appliances, and a center island. At the back of the home is a sophisticated formal dining room, with a beamed ceiling overhead, a decorative fireplace, and a china cabinet. The fabulous primary suite has access to the sprawling back patio, with plenty of room for BBQing and seating. Off the generous bedroom is a walk-in closet, and a sleek bath with a glass-enclosed shower with rain showerheads, marble tile, and double vanity. A bonus room on the lower level is perfect for an office, plus shared laundry. Leased garage parking 2 blocks away, $385/mo. Blocks from the Presidio, Alta Plaza and Presidio Heights Playground, and shops and dining on nearby Sacramento St.

Residence 705 features brand-new Oak flooring in the living room, plush carpet in the bedroom, a fully equipped kitchen with Bosch appliances including the gas range, custom-designed quartz countertops, white soft closet cabinets with porcelain tile backsplash, and amazing city views. The bathroom is finished with custom-designed floating vanities with quartz countertops, stylish, warm grey cabinets, and porcelain tile flooring.OneEleven is a luxurious boutique condo complex offering an expansive roof terrace with lounge seating, BBQ Island, a dining area, City skyline views, an exclusive resident lobby with a secure package room, and bike storage. The building is located in the center of SoMa - within walking distance of the Financial District, a brand-new Whole Foods Market, Trader Joe, Westfield Mall, Target, Caltrain, and easy access to the Bay Bridge, 101, and 280 Hwys.

Major Price Improvement! This Jr.1BR residence is the quintessential San Francisco home with a sun-bathed Bay Window overlooking the buzz of neighborhood. Owners will find tailored finishes such as central A/C, double-paned windows, an oversized walk-in closet; full kitchen with full size Bosch appliances, LG washer/dryer and a contemporary bathroom with floating vanity and deep soaking tub. This home measures 625 SF providing plenty of space for city life. 2238 Market amenities include Latch access throughout the building, bike storage, a rooftop with iconic views stretching from Sutro Tower to the Bay and Transamerica Building.*Photos are of Model Home #210

Located in the premiere Marina neighborhood, 3235 Gough Street No. 301 is a beautiful, top floor 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom TIC with garage parking on one of the best blocks of San Francisco. Situated in a boutique, 14-unit building, this move-in ready home boasts an open floor plan with gorgeous original hardwood floors and an ideal layout. The kitchen with countertop seating overlooks the light & bright living space - perfect for entertaining guests. The bedroom is flooded with natural light, and a peek-a-boo Golden Gate Bridge view. The home is complete with 1 car deeded garage parking (compact space) and storage unit in the garage. This iconic 1920s building features a roof deck with stunning GGB, Marin, and water views, a large shared garden with BBQ area, elegant lobby, and exquisite period details. This A+ location can't be beat with a 95 Walk & Bike Score. You are steps to Fort Mason, Marina Green, Chestnut shops, restaurants, and nightlife. Welcome home!

Welcome to a top floor, beautifully updated condo on a quaint, tree-lined block. This light-filled, home reflects the style, sophistication + elegance of SF; it''s the definition of true pride of ownership. The open floor plan, remodeled kitchen + bath, and 2 spacious BRs are enhanced by the panoramic views of downtown and the surrounding hills which will be your reward as the new owner. Hardwood floors, period detailing, recessed lighting + beautiful large windows allow for sought-after views of the City.  Providing great separation of space, the comfortable front bedrooms connect seamlessly to the rear of the home.   1 BR features a decorative fireplace, built-in bookshelves and a bay window.  The 2nd BR has a large custom closet.   The dreamy kitchen has stainless steel appliances, a built-in wine rack, a separate eating area, and direct access to the sunny, lushly landscaped, shared backyard.  The BA is a split bath, promoting privacy. This elegant flat features an additional laundry room in the rear of the unit with a newer w/d, deeded storage, and 1 car garage parking.  This 3 unit Edwardian is very well maintained + funded. Here you are merely moments away from the spirited Castro district, its wonderful shops + transportation.

Remarks  Enjoy a life of luxury - fine dining, trendy nightlife, and spa-like amenities - in your waterfront casa where South Beach meets the marina. Paint the town at night, then spend a slow morning sipping your coffee on your balcony as the sun rises over the Bay. Take the dogs to any of the nearby parks or check out some of San Francisco's favorite trails, then hit the farmer's market on your way home. Choose an evening outfit from your many walk-in closets so you can wow your friends tonight. Treat them to a home cooked meal from your modern kitchen with its anchored granite countertops and bar seating and entertain them in the loft-like living and dining areas where soaring 2-story windows look out on the private patio. After dinner, you'll cross the street to catch a fun Giants game, and tomorrow will be all relaxation. This building has it all - a gym, pool, spa, and sauna, plus an outdoor fire pit and a communal garden with treelined views of the ballpark.

OFFERS Friday 03/24 @ 2:00 pm  Delightful Edwardian Condo with two bedrooms, one split bath + office. Lovely living room with a fireplace, Bay windows overlooking lush backyard, open floor plan remodel kitchen features a large peninsula, Viking Pro range and adjoining dining area with custom built-in bench. Laundry room with LG W/dryer and direct access to a sweet shared backyard, deeded downstairs bonus/storage room. One car parking. Located close to Duboce Park, Mission Dolores, Castro, Hayes Valley and Lower Haight. This property is a commuter's delight with easy access to Muni, shuttle bus and freeway access.

Price improvement! Enjoy resort style living in the best South Beach location! The Towers at 88 King offers an outdoor pool and spa, bbq area, lush sheltered courtyard, gym overlooking the Marina, and 24-hr. door person. The proximity to the Embarcadero and Oracle Park provides a lifestyle geared to walking, biking, kayaking and sailing, as well as shopping and dining at iconic San Francisco restaurants. The north tower condo gets abundant natural light and has views of Downtown, the Bay Bridge, and Twin Peaks. A spacious living room/dining area opens onto a balcony perfect for morning coffee or evening wine while watching the lights come up over the City and Bay. The open kitchen features a breakfast bar, wine cooler, stainless appliances, and granite countertops. The large primary bedroom has space for an office nook, downtown views, a limestone bath with a washer/dryer, and a walk-in closet. The second bedroom has outlooks to the view balcony.  A second full bath accommodates guests. Cherry hardwood floors, carpeted bedrooms, floor-to-ceiling windows, and freshly painted throughout. One car parking and storage included. Easy to show by appointment with advanced notice.

1 bedroom Below Market Rate (BMR) housing opportunity available at 112% Area Median Income (AMI). Maximum income for 1 person = $108,650; 2 = $124,125; 3 = $139,650, etc. Must be 1st-time homebuyer & income eligible. Unit available thru the Mayor's Office of Housing and Community Development (MOHCD) & subject to resale controls, monitoring & other restrictions. Unit will be listed on DAHLIA, the SF Housing Portal (https://housing.sfgov.org) starting on the application date, 11-1-2022. Visit https://housing.sfgov.org for application & program info. Application, loan pre-approval, and homebuyer education verification due on 11-23-2022. Fair Housing Opportunity.

2110-2112 Pine Street was originally built sometime between 1900 - 1913 as a 2-unit building, but by the mid-1960s, had been divided into 4 units. 2110 Pine #A is a lower, front condo, with 1-bedroom and 1 recently updated bathroom, plus a decorative fireplace with a wood mantel in the living room. Although it faces Pine Street, the windows have an extra interior window to soften any noise. Rooms are generous in size, and a walk-in closet in the foyer offers ample storage space. The lack of parking is offset by the fact that the condo has a Walk Score of 99% and is only 2 blocks from multiple amenities along Fillmore Street.

A sun-filled, 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom condominium with parking at the Sutterfield!  Wonderful layout with each en suite bedroom located at opposite sides of the unit.
